{"word":"ἀπάγω","slug":"ἀπάγω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀπάγω</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀπό\">ἀπό</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἄγω\">ἄγω</a></el>]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘take/lead (away)’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp> <i>lead off:</i></b> of an animal taken to water <b><a href='B:490 13:15'>Lk 13:15</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ abs.\">abs.</a> of Paul taken out of the hands of his captors <b><a href='B:510 24:6'>Ac 24:6</a> [7] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a>;</b> as term in various phases of judicial process <b><a href='B:470 26:57'>Mt 26:57</a>; <a href='B:470 27:2'>27:2</a>, <a href='B:470 27:31'>31</a>; <a href='B:480 14:53'>Mk 14:53</a>; <a href='B:480 15:16'>15:16</a>; <a href='B:490 21:12'>Lk 21:12</a>; <a href='B:490 22:66'>22:66</a>; <a href='B:490 23:26'>23:26</a>; <a href='B:510 12:19'>Ac 12:19</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp> <i>divert from the correct way</i> <a href='B:530 12:2'>1 Cor 12:2</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ intr.\">intr.</a> in imagery of a road and geographical direction: <b><i>go/lead (off)</i> <a href='B:470 7:13'>Mt 7:13f</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀπάγχω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀπαίδευτος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}